President Obama held a video conference with British Prime Minister David Cameron, French President Francois Hollande, and German Chancellor Angela Merkel to discuss the situation in Syria and the refugee crisis in Europe. They welcomed the prospect of a cessation of hostilities in Syria and called on all parties to implement it faithfully. They also emphasized the importance of a political transition in Syria for lasting peace. The leaders discussed ways to alleviate the humanitarian crisis in Syria and the importance of NATO's mission and coordination between Greece and Turkey to manage the flow of migrants into Europe.